🌐 Web Development — Clean Beginner Notes
🔹 1. MERN Stack (Full Stack Development)

MERN = Complete app development stack

M → MongoDB → Database (stores data)
E → Express.js → Backend framework (handles requests)
R → React.Js → Frontend (UI)
N → Node.js → Runtime (runs JS on server)



🔹 2. Three Pillars of Web Dev
HTML → Structure (skeleton)
CSS → Design (looks)
JavaScript → Logic (brain)


🔹 3. Other Stacks
MEAN
MERN (React instead of Angular)
Java Full Stack



🔹 4. Teams in Web Development
Developers → Build features
Testing Team → Find bugs
DevOps Team → Deployment & hosting
Support Team → Fix issues after release



🔹 5. SDLC (Software Development Life Cycle)

Different ways to build software:

Waterfall → Step-by-step (rigid)
Agile → Iterative (most used today)
Spiral → Risk-focused
Iterative → Repeat improvements
Incremental → Build in parts
V-Model → Testing + development parallel
RAD → Fast development



🔹 6. URL (Uniform Resource Locator)

Example:

https://education.rohanAcademy.edu/FullStack

Breakdown:

https → Protocol
rohanAcademy → Domain (main name)
education → Subdomain
.edu → TLD (Top Level Domain)
/FullStack → Path
🔹 7. Protocols (Communication Rules)
HTTP → Normal web communication
HTTPS → Secure version
TCP → Reliable data transfer
UDP → Fast but unreliable
SMTP → Email sending
FTP → File transfer
IP → Identifies devices (IPv4 / IPv6)



🔹 8. Domain & Subdomain
Domain:
Unique name of a website
Example: google, amazon
Subdomain:
Extensions of main domain
Example:
mail.google.com
maps.google.com
🔹 9. TLD (Top-Level Domain)

Examples:

.com → Commercial
.org → Organization
.edu → Education
.in → India
.uk → United Kingdom
